              "mainEntity": [
                {
                  "@type": "Question",
                  "name": "What is the difference between Monel 400 and pure nickel or pure copper?",
                  "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "Monel 400 is an alloy made from a mixture of various elements (mainly nickel and copper), while pure nickel and pure copper contain no other elements. In terms of properties, pure copper and pure nickel are relatively soft, while Monel 400 not only achieves higher strength through alloying but also gains better corrosion resistance and certain high-temperature performance."
                  }
                },
                {
                  "@type": "Question",
                  "name": "What is the difference between copper-nickel alloys and nickel-copper alloys?",
                  "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "Copper-nickel alloys are copper alloys, with copper as the main element. Nickel-copper alloys are nickel alloys, with nickel as the main element and copper as a minor element. Their properties are significantly different, so please carefully consider your needs before purchasing."
                  }
                },
                {
                  "@type": "Question",
                  "name": "What are the roles of the main elements in Monel 400 alloys?",
                  "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "Nickel contributes to a more stable structure in Monel 400, enabling it to withstand certain high temperatures while maintaining good ductility. Copper provides the alloy with better corrosion resistance and better electrical conductivity."
                  }
                },
                {
                  "@type": "Question",
                  "name": "How can I purchase your products?",
                  "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "You can send us your requirements directly via email: sales@aeether.com, or fill out the form at the bottom of the page and submit it. Our sales team will send you a detailed quotation. If you are interested in our offer, you can send us a PO (Purchase Order). We will provide you with a PI (Proforma Invoice) for payment. We will begin material production upon receiving the prepayment. We will notify you as soon as the materials are complete."
                  }
                },
