            <section id="faq-page">
                <h2 class="grade-h2"><span>FAQ</span></h2>
                <div id="faq-content">
                    <div id="faq-box">
                        <div class="faq-frame faq-v">
                            <div class="q-frame">
                                <div class="q-t">Q</div>
                                <p class="q-text">What is the difference between Monel 400 and pure nickel or pure copper?</p>
                                <div class="q-line"><div></div></div>                                
                            </div>
                            <div class="a-frame">
                                <div class="a-t">A</div>
                                <img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/image/faq/pmi.jpg" alt="PMI test">
                                <p class="a-text">Monel 400 is an alloy made from a mixture of various elements (mainly nickel and copper), while pure nickel and pure copper contain no other elements. In terms of properties, pure copper and pure nickel are relatively soft, while Monel 400 not only achieves higher strength through alloying but also gains better corrosion resistance and certain high-temperature performance.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-frame faq-v">
                            <div class="q-frame">
                                <div class="q-t">Q</div>
                                <p class="q-text">What is the difference between copper-nickel alloys and nickel-copper alloys?</p>
                                <div class="q-line"><div></div></div>                                
                            </div>
                            <div class="a-frame">
                                <div class="a-t">A</div>
                                <img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/image/faq/seamless-pipe-tube-1.jpg" alt="Seamless Pipe & Tube">
                                <p class="a-text">Copper-nickel alloys are copper alloys, with copper as the main element. Nickel-copper alloys are nickel alloys, with nickel as the main element and copper as a minor element. Their properties are significantly different, so please carefully consider your needs before purchasing.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-frame faq-u">
                            <div class="q-frame">
                                <div class="q-t">Q</div>
                                <p class="q-text">What are the roles of the main elements in Monel 400 alloys?</p>
                                <div class="q-line"><div></div></div>                                
                            </div>
                            <div class="a-frame">
                                <div class="a-t">A</div>
                                <img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/image/faq/chemical-analysis.jpg" alt="Chemical Analysis">
                                <p class="a-text">Nickel contributes to a more stable structure in Monel 400, enabling it to withstand certain high temperatures while maintaining good ductility. Copper provides the alloy with better corrosion resistance and better electrical conductivity.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-frame faq-u">
                            <div class="q-frame">
                                <div class="q-t">Q</div>
                                <p class="q-text">How can I purchase your products?</p>
                                <div class="q-line"><div></div></div>                                
                            </div>
                            <div class="a-frame">
                                <div class="a-t">A</div>
                                <img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/image/faq/package-1.jpg" alt="Package">
                                <p class="a-text">You can send us your requirements directly via email: <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="5e2d3f323b2d1e3f3b3b2a363b2c703d3133">[email&#160;protected]</a>, or fill out the form at the bottom of the page and submit it. Our sales team will send you a detailed quotation. If you are interested in our offer, you can send us a PO (Purchase Order). We will provide you with a PI (Proforma Invoice) for payment. We will begin material production upon receiving the prepayment. We will notify you as soon as the materials are complete.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-frame faq-u">
                            <div class="q-frame">
                                <div class="q-t">Q</div>
                                <p class="q-text">Why do different products have different mechanical properties?</p>
                                <div class="q-line"><div></div></div>                                
                            </div>
                            <div class="a-frame">
                                <div class="a-t">A</div>
                                <img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/image/faq/mechanical-properties-3.jpg" alt="Mechanical Properties">
                                <p class="a-text">Different mechanical properties may depend on many factors: <br>1) Different product processes; <br>2) Different cold working and heat treatment methods; <br>3) Different dimensions.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-frame faq-u">
                            <div class="q-frame">
                                <div class="q-t">Q</div>
                                <p class="q-text">Is Monel 400 material suitable for room temperature or high temperature?</p>
                                <div class="q-line"><div></div></div>                                
                            </div>
                            <div class="a-frame">
                                <div class="a-t">A</div>
                                <img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/image/faq/plate-2.jpg" alt="Plate">
                                <p class="a-text">Although Monel 400 can withstand certain high temperatures, its high-temperature resistance is limited. Therefore, Monel 400 is generally used in some room-temperature applications, typically marine vessels.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-frame faq-u">
                            <div class="q-frame">
                                <div class="q-t">Q</div>
                                <p class="q-text">What is purity?</p>
                                <div class="q-line"><div></div></div>                                
                            </div>
                            <div class="a-frame">
                                <div class="a-t">A</div>
                                <img loading="lazy" src="/AEETHER/image/faq/strip-1.jpg" alt="Strip">
                                <p class="a-text">Purity is an indicator of the proportion of impurity or harmful elements in an alloy. The lower the proportion of impurity or harmful elements, the higher the purity, and thus the better the material's performance.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section id="media-page" class="fold3" >
                <h2 class="grade-h2"><span>Related Article</span></h2>
